<item>
            <title>[CXF-8007] HTTP Signature adds an extra &quot;Signature&quot; component to the Signature header</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-8007</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HTTP Signature adds an extra &quot;Signature&quot; component to the Signature header: e.g.:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Headers: {Content-Type=[application/xml], Accept=[application/xml], Signature=[Signature keyId=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;alice-key-id&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,algorithm=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;rsa-sha512&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,headers=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;accept&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,signature=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;]}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is because the Tomitribe Signatures class has a toString() method which assumes that the output is to be used in an Authorization header. However in CXF our code instead uses the Signature HTTP header (section 4 of the spec). Instead it should look like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Headers: {Content-Type=[application/xml], Accept=[application/xml], Signature=[keyId=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;alice-key-id&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,algorithm=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;rsa-sha512&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,headers=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;accept&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,signature=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;]}

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
